# Deployment & Operations (Vercel)

## Hosting
- Deploy via Vercel connected to the GitHub repo. `main` → production, PRs → preview.
- Build command: `next build`. Output: static Next.js site served by Vercel.

## Environment
- Client-visible env vars must be prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
- Configure image domains in `next.config.js` if using remote images; prefer `/public` assets when possible.

## Quality gates
- Enable Next.js ESLint during CI/Vercel builds.
- Treat TypeScript errors as build errors once TS is enabled.

## Performance
- Use `next/image` for responsive images; provide `sizes` for hero/gallery.
- Leverage static generation. Avoid server-side rendering unless necessary.

## SEO & Metadata
- Provide `robots.txt` and `sitemap.xml` when URLs stabilize.
- Ensure proper Open Graph/Twitter meta on the homepage.

## Monitoring
- Enable Vercel Analytics (optional). Monitor core web vitals in previews before promotion.

